* Iron didn't stop.
< Go away.>
It felt like no one cared, not even Prowl.
All they cared about was that stupid city, ripping up the ship she'd called 
home and none of them cared.
She had never hand a home and just when she had tried to settle in and was 
feeling comfortable there they had to tare it down.
No one cared.
But why did she expect them to?
She sighed.
< Gotta be something to do with this body. Maybe that so called PMS or 
something.>
She lied to herself.  But she was commander and even though that was just a 
name and meant nothing, she thought thst she would at least mean something.*
